President Obama met with newly appointed Special Envoy for Sudan Ambassador Princeton Lyman at the White House. They discussed the critical situation in Sudan, including concerns over the bombings in Darfur and the situation in Abyei. The President expressed his commitment to establishing two viable states in northern and South Sudan in July. Ambassador Lyman was tasked with increasing efforts towards achieving a lasting ceasefire and political settlement in Darfur. He will make two trips to the region in the next month, focusing on Comprehensive Peace Agreement implementation and Darfur.